      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The escrow company holds the money like a highly trusted banker, not just hoarding it while waiting for closing. They adhere to strict trust accounting protocols, keeping your funds completely separate from the company's operational money. This money is officially designated as a liability for them, meaning they are legally obligated to release it specifically upon the contractual fulfillment of conditions. This regulatory oversight ensures the funds are secure right up until closing day.",
      "source": "target",
